ass injector for the system class loader.\n   305\t         *\n   306\t         * @return A class injector for the system class loader.\n   307\t         */\n   308\t        public static ClassInjector ofSystemClassLoader() {\n   309\t            return new UsingReflection(ClassLoader.getSystemClassLoader());\n   310\t        }\n   311\t\n   312\t        /**\n   313\t         * A dispatcher for accessing a {@link ClassLoader} reflectively.\n   314\t         */\n   315\t        protected interface Dispatcher {\n   316\t\n   317\t            /**\n   318\t             * Indicates a class that is currently not defined.\n   319\t             */\n   320\t            @AlwaysNull\n   321\t            Class<?> UNDEFINED = null;\n   322\t\n   323\t            /**\n   324\t             * Returns the lock for loading the specified class.\n   325\t             *\n   326\t             * @param classLoader the class loader to inject the class into.\n   327\t             * @param name        The name of the class.\n   328\t             * @return The lock for loading this class.\n   329\t             */\n   330\t            Object getClassLoadingLock(ClassLoader classLoader, String name);\n   331\t\n   332\t            /**\n   333\t             * Looks up a class from the given class loader.\n   334\t             *\n   335\t             * @param classLoader The class loader for which a class should be located.\n   336\t             * @param name        The binary name of the class that should be located.\n   337\t             * @return The class for the binary name or {@code null} if no such class is defined for the provided class loader.\n   338\t             */\n   339\t            @MaybeNull\n   340\t            Class<?> findClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String name);\n   341\t\n   342\t            /**\n   343\t             * Defines a class for the given class loader.\n   344\t             *\n   345\t             * @param classLoader          The class loader for which a new class should be defined.\n   346\t             * @param name                 The binary name of the class that should be defined.\n   347\t             * @param binaryRepresentation The binary representation of the class.\n   348\t             * @param protectionDomain     The protection domain for the defined class.\n   349\t             * @return The defined, loaded class.\n   350\t             */\n   351\t            Class<?> defineClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String name, byte[] binaryRepresentation, @MaybeNull ProtectionDomain protectionDomain);\n   352\t\n   353\t            /**\n   354\t             * Looks up a package from a class loader. If the operation is not supported, falls back to {@link #getPackage(ClassLoader, String)}\n   355\t             *\n   356\t             * @param classLoader The class loader to query.\n   357\t             * @param name        The binary name of the package.\n   358\t             * @return The package for the given name as defined by the provided class loader or {@code null} if no such package exists.\n   359\t             */\n   360\t            @MaybeNull\n   361\t            Package getDefinedPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String name);\n   362\t\n   363\t            /**\n   364\t             * Looks up a package from a class loader or its ancestor.\n   365\t             *\n   366\t             * @param classLoader The class loader to query.\n   367\t             * @param name        The binary name of the package.\n   368\t             * @return The package for the given name as defined by the provided class loader or its ancestor, or {@code null} if no such package exists.\n   369\t             */\n   370\t            @MaybeNull\n   371\t            Package getPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String name);\n   372\t\n   373\t            /**\n   374\t             * Defines a package for the given class loader.\n   375\t             *\n   376\t             * @param classLoader           The class loader for which a package is to be defined.\n   377\t             * @param name                  The binary name of the package.\n   378\t             * @param specificationTitle    The specification title of the package or {@code null} if no specification title exists.\n   379\t             * @param specificationVersion  The specification version of the package or {@code null} if no specification version exists.\n   380\t             * @param specificationVendor   The specification vendor of the package or {@code null} if no specification vendor exists.\n   381\t             * @param implementationTitle   The implementation title of the package or {@code null} if no implementation title exists.\n   382\t             * @param implementationVersion The implementation version of the package or {@code null} if no implementation version exists.\n   383\t             * @param implementationVendor  The implementation vendor of the package or {@code null} if no implementation vendor exists.\n   384\t             * @param sealBase              The seal base URL or {@code null} if the package should not be sealed.\n   385\t             * @return The defined package.\n   386\t             */\n   387\t            Package definePackage(ClassLoader classLoader,\n   388\t                                  String name,\n   389\t                                  @MaybeNull String specificationTitle,\n   390\t                                  @MaybeNull String specificationVersion,\n   391\t                                  @MaybeNull String specificationVendor,\n   392\t                                  @MaybeNull String implementationTitle,\n   393\t                                  @MaybeNull String implementationVersion,\n   394\t                                  @MaybeNull String implementationVendor,\n   395\t                                  @MaybeNull URL sealBase);\n   396\t\n   397\t            /**\n   398\t             * Initializes a dispatcher to make non-accessible APIs accessible.\n   399\t             */\n   400\t            interface Initializable {\n   401\t\n   402\t                /**\n   403\t                 * Indicates if this dispatcher is available.\n   404\t                 *\n   405\t                 * @return {@code true} if this dispatcher is available.\n   406\t                 */\n   407\t                boolean isAvailable();\n   408\t\n   409\t                /**\n   410\t                 * Initializes this dispatcher.\n   411\t                 *\n   412\t                 * @return The initialized dispatcher.\n   413\t                 */\n   414\t                Dispatcher initialize();\n   415\t\n   416\t                /**\n   417\t                 * Represents an unsuccessfully loaded method lookup.\n   418\t                 */\n   419\t                @HashCodeAndEqualsPlugin.Enhance\n   420\t                class Unavailable implements Dispatcher, Initializable {\n   421\t\n   422\t                    /**\n   423\t                     * The reason why this dispatcher is not available.\n   424\t                     */\n   425\t                    private final String message;\n   426\t\n   427\t                    /**\n   428\t                     * Creates a new faulty reflection store.\n   429\t                     *\n   430\t                     * @param message The reason why this dispatcher is not available.\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1781078390526}]}
