[assistant] Fixed the native-image metadata parsing error.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Root cause:
[assistant] - `reachability-metadata.json` was created as:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```json
[assistant] []
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] but Native Image expects the top-level reachability metadata file to be a JSON object.
[assistant] 
[assistant] Updated:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```text
[assistant] metadata/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/reachability-metadata.json
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] to:
[assistant] 
[assistant] ```json
[assistant] {}
[assistant] ```
[assistant] 
[assistant] This keeps the coordinate selectable while providing valid empty reachability metadata.
[assistant-event] text_end
